name: Nidalee
title: the Bestial Huntress
shortBio: Raised in the deepest jungle, Nidalee is a master tracker who can shapeshift into a ferocious cougar at will. Neither wholly woman nor beast, she viciously defends her territory from any and all trespassers, with carefully placed traps and deft spear throws. She cripples her quarry before pouncing on them in feline form—the lucky few who survive tell tales of a wild woman with razor-sharp instincts, and even sharper claws...

skins.name: Snow Bunny Nidalee
skins.description: A fierce warrior who makes her home in the winter forest, Nidalee has little interest in Snowdown parties. Instead, she prefers to spend her time protecting cheerful woodland creatures from trappers and intruders, giving her furry friends a reason for the season.

skins.name: Leopard Nidalee
skins.description: Nidalee roams the tall grasses and bubbling tar pits of her home, a prehistoric savannah teeming with natural magic. She protects her leap of leopards by taking the appearance of their hunters, deceiving and disarming human threats with her wild skill.

skins.name: French Maid Nidalee
skins.description: Armed with a diverting maid outfit, a sunny disposition, and a vast knowledge of cleaning techniques, Nidalee catburgles her wealthy customers without them being any the wiser. She does it all for her kitties, who have grown used to some very high quality scratching posts.

skins.name: Pharaoh Nidalee
skins.description: Worshiped as a god-queen of the Great Desert, Nidalee is the avatar of the glorious cat-god, Sypakaa. As war tears through the land, Nidalee will do whatever it takes to protect her city and her temple from those who would dare threaten them.

skins.name: Bewitching Nidalee
skins.description: She is a cat. That is a hat. Legally, we're not allowed to put those two thoughts together.

skins.name: Headhunter Nidalee
skins.description: There are those who still ask: between man and beast, who is the better hunter? With her alien biology allowing her to embody both, Nidalee of the Headhunters answers that question with, “I am.”

skins.name: Warring Kingdoms Nidalee
skins.description: Of the legends surrounding Nidalee, it is difficult to know what is true and what is mere myth. Some within the Warring Kingdoms say she fights with the wild ferocity of a white tiger, that the tiger's spirit dwells within her heart. Others believe she is the white tiger, that she can become the beast itself.

skins.name: Super Galaxy Nidalee
skins.description: Of the new class of Super Galaxy cadets, Nidalee—with her exceptional skill for throwing projectiles through zero-gravity—shows the most promise. As the Spider Queen continues her reign of terror, the team will need Nidalee's cunning tactics and keen hunting instincts if they want to save the galaxy.

skins.name: Dawnbringer Nidalee
skins.description: Both a celestial beast and a dawn-walking primordial, Nidalee rules over the restorative calm of the natural world. She guards the land's remaining peaceful places, bringing light and order to the mortal creatures under her care.

skins.name: Cosmic Huntress Nidalee
skins.description: A cosmic tracker and ferocious hunter, Nidalee travels the galaxy in an eternal hunt, shifting her shape to hide among the sky's wandering stars. Tasked with finding and caring for newborn stars, she is dedicated to defending them from the ever hungry Dark Star corruptants.

skins.name: DWG Nidalee
skins.description: Honoring Canyon's winning performance as Nidalee during the 2020 World Championship.

skins.name: Ocean Song Nidalee
skins.description: The Ocean Song Festival is lucky to have Nidalee as its performer stylist, with her fashion guides selling almost as much as her albums, but in reality she's here as a featured part of Yone's show. She was the first person he showed his lyrics to, and it's her honor to lend them her voice.

skins.name: Kittalee
skins.description: Adorable squeaky toy or deadly weapon? In Nidalee's claws, a Friendly Fish (TM) can be both!

skins.name: La Ilusión Nidalee
skins.description: A jaguar leader of her own pack, Nidalee was both feared and respected by her neighboring humans. When she fell to a group of hunters for protecting her family, the shared love not just from her pack, but from her neighbors, reincarnated Nidalee as an Eidola Vida. With the power to assume both jaguar and human form now, she watches over her kin from afar.

skins.name: Spirit Blossom Nidalee
skins.description: The Tale of the Wise Cat is told in many ways across Ionia, but all begin the same: “There once was a cat who lived far beyond her years...” Though age brought power, allowing her to shift form between feline and mortal, her questions only deepened. She searched for answers, unaware that the wisdom she yearned for had always lived within.

passive.name: Prowl
passive.description:
Moving through brush increases Nidalee's Move Speed by 10% for 2 seconds, increased to 30% toward visible enemy champions within 1400 range.

Hitting champions or monsters with Javelin Toss or Bushwhack triggers a Hunt, granting True Sight of them for 4 seconds. During this time, Nidalee gains 10% Move Speed (increased to 30% toward the Hunted target) and her Takedown and Pounce are enhanced against them.

spells.name: Javelin Toss / Takedown
spells.description: In human form, Nidalee throws a spiked javelin at her target that gains damage as it flies.  As a cougar, her next attack will attempt to fatally wound her target, dealing more damage the less life they have.
spells.dynamicDescription: <keywordMajor>Human Form:</keywordMajor> Nidalee throws her javelin, dealing <magicDamage>@HumanMinimumDamage@ magic damage</magicDamage>, increased up to <magicDamage>@HumanMaximumDamage@ magic damage</magicDamage> based on distance flown.@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@

spells.name: Bushwhack / Pounce
spells.description: In human form, Nidalee lays a trap for unwary opponents that, when sprung, damages and reveals its target. As a cougar, she jumps in a direction, dealing damage in an area where she lands.
spells.dynamicDescription:
Human Form: Nidalee places an invisible trap for 2 minutes. When an enemy walks over it, they are dealt @DamagePerSecond@ magic damage per second for @Effect3Amount@ seconds.

@MaxTraps@ traps may be active at once.@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@

spells.name: Primal Surge / Swipe
spells.description: In human form, Nidalee channels the spirit of the cougar to heal her allies and imbue them with Attack Speed for a short duration. As a cougar, she claws in a direction, dealing damage to enemies in front of her.
spells.dynamicDescription: <keywordMajor>Human Form:</keywordMajor> Nidalee restores <healing>@TotalHealing@ Health</healing> increased up to <healing>@MaxHealing@</healing> based on missing Health and grants them <attackSpeed>@BonusAS*100@% Attack Speed</attackSpeed> for @ASDuration@ seconds.@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@

spells.name: Aspect Of The Cougar
spells.description: Nidalee transforms into a cougar, gaining new abilities.
spells.dynamicDescription:
Passive: While in Human Form, applying Hunted refreshes this Ability's Cooldown.

Human Form: Nidalee transforms into Cougar Form, gaining melee Attacks and replacing her Active Abilities.

Cougar Form: Nidalee transforms into Human Form, gaining ranged Attacks and replacing her Active Abilities.@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@
